```julia
function timezone_bumper(dt, bump = 3)
    if !isa(dt, DateTime))
        throw(ArgumentError("Input must be a DateTime type")))
    end

    return dt + convert(Duration, bump * 60 * 60))
end
```

This function `timezone_bumper` takes a `DateTime` and an optional `bump` parameter (defaulting to 3 hours). It checks if the input is a `DateTime`, throwing an error for `Date` types.

The function then adds the specified number of hours to the input timestamp.
